720780f-a.title: Manhattan: Lafayette Street - Bleecker Street
720780f-a.text:
Lafayette Street (Elm Street), south from but not including Bleecker
Street, showing construction work in progress on the Interborough Rapid
Transit Co. (I.R.T.) subway, after the demolition of houses which formerly
stood there. Lafayette Street was created as a result of the joining
together of Lafayette Place, which terminated at Great Jones Street, with
Elm Street, which commenced at a point slightly south of Jersey Street.
This necessitated the razing of many buildings which occupied the area
between the above mentioned two streets. The new thoroughfare was given
its present name several years later.
December 1900.
Board of Transportation Photograph.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
William B. Parsons Collection.

Imany houses in a northerly direction from Eln Street, which terminated at
